{"tid":2197362,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"<<花木蘭>>強國上映在即 但強國唔准報導","createTime":"2020-09-10T14:18:23.000Z","updateTime":"2020-09-12T07:28:47.000Z","uid":270889,"like":10,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":5,"replies":[{"pid":"4e74b3ba10e5dbb43bf5f2eb7ecf00ad604f9ef0","tid":2197362,"uid":270889,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-09-10T14:18:23.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://twitter.com/brendagoh_/status/1303990610680930304?s=20\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fbrendagoh_%2Fstatus%2F1303990610680930304%3Fs%3D20&d=u5s3JLQ1HZhTjCUFZ9m1FPrgBFspSC5jYnxvlVik22g%3D&h=4f230000\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fbrendagoh_%2Fstatus%2F1303990610680930304%3Fs%3D20&h=3a956916\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://twitter.com/brendagoh_/status/1303990610680930304?s=20</a><br />\n<br />\nChinese authorities have told major media outlets<span class=\"red\"> not to cover Walt Disney Co&rsquo;s release of &ldquo;Mulan&rdquo;</span>, in an order issued after controversy erupted overseas over the film&rsquo;s links with the Xinjiang region, four people familiar with matter told Reuters.<br />\n<br />\nSet to open in local theatres on Friday, Disney (DIS.N)<span class=\"red\"> had high hopes for Mulan in China, but starving it of publicity in the country&rsquo;s strictly censored media would be another blow</span> to the $200 million production. Starring big-name Chinese-born actors - Jet Li, Gong Li, Donnie Yen and Liu Yifei - and based on a Chinese folk story, Mulan was tailored to appeal to audiences in China, the world&rsquo;s second-largest movie market.<br />\n(迪士尼原本好高期望 依家再受另一打擊) <img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/clap.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\nBut mixed reviews online and capacity limits in theatres due to coronavirus prevention measures were likely to weigh on its box office performance, even before major media outlets received a notice telling them to <span class=\"red\">refrain from covering the movie</span>.<br />\nThree sources told Reuters media outlets had received the notice, two of whom said it was sent by the <span class=\"red\">Cyberspace Administration of China</span>. A fourth source at a major Chinese newspaper said he received a text message with a similar order from a senior colleague. <span class=\"red\">No reason was given in the notice</span>, but the sources said they believed it was because of the overseas backlash over the film&rsquo;s links to Xinjiang. <span class=\"red\">Neither the Cyberspace Administration or Disney immediately responded to requests for comment.</span><br />\n<span class=\"orange\">(總之就唔比啦 黨要你做咩洗咩解釋 迪士尼當然都不得異議)</span><br />\n<br />\nPartly shot in Xinjiang, <span class=\"red\">Mulan&rsquo;s credits included thanks to the authorities there</span>, which prompted calls overseas for a boycott of the movie. China&rsquo;s clampdown on ethnic Uighurs and other Muslims in Xinjiang has been criticised by some governments, including the United States, and human rights groups.<br />\n<br />\nDisney had worked to ensure Mulan tested well with Chinese audiences, and the company&rsquo;s chief financial officer told investors on Wednesday that it was <span class=\"red\">&ldquo;very pleased&rdquo; with the initial results</span> of its release elsewhere.<br />\n<span class=\"orange\">(迪士尼表示滿意成績 係有苦自己知/奶得好開心)<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></span><br />\n<br />\nMulan is likely to be shown on more than 40% of China&rsquo;s screens on Friday, according to data from Maoyan, a Tencent-backed ticketing platform. Chinese theatres are currently limiting capacity, typically at 50 percent. <span class=\"red\">The film had sold 9.78 million yuan</span> ($1.43 million) worth of tickets as of Thursday afternoon, accounting for 55% of all ticket sales sold across China for Friday&rsquo;s shows.<br />\n<span class=\"orange\">(如果無水份又好似真係票房唔錯)<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></span><br />\n<br />\nThe film, which many have already seen online, <span class=\"red\">has received a 4.7 score out of 10 on popular social media site Douban</span>, where users leave reviews of films, books and music.<br />\n<span class=\"orange\">(邊個咁大膽比咁低分 要爆上門用黨安法拉人)<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></span><br />\n<br />\n全文:<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/article/us-film-mulan-china-exclusive/exclusive-china-bars-media-coverage-of-disneys-mulan-after-xinjiang-backlash-sources-idUSKBN2611FP\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-film-mulan-china-exclusive%2Fexclusive-china-bars-media-coverage-of-disneys-mulan-after-xinjiang-backlash-sources-idUSKBN2611FP&d=u5s3JLQ1HZhTjCUFZ9m1FPrgBFspSC5jYnxvlVik22g%3D&h=30d5c234\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-film-mulan-china-exclusive%2Fexclusive-china-bars-media-coverage-of-disneys-mulan-after-xinjiang-backlash-sources-idUSKBN2611FP&h=1a357d94\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.reuters.com/article/us-film-mulan-china-exclusive/exclusive-china-bars-media-coverage-of-disneys-mulan-after-xinjiang-backlash-sources-idUSKBN2611FP</a><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<span class=\"violet\">提防fake news<br />\n大家唔好標題都唔睇 咩都推 we are better than this</span><br />\n<del>小鳳姐出場：花木蘭中國唔比上影</del><br />\n- 分享自 LIHKG 討論區<br />\n<a href=\"https://lih.kg/2197304\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://lih.kg/2197304</a>"},{"pid":"02b9a38c0627258977ea7edf3e4c129ebc717e3e","tid":2197362,"uid":159271,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-09-10T14:20:00.000Z","msg":"推呢個"},{"pid":"05782cad666950820e3fc7034712e359faa7a480","tid":2197362,"uid":270889,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"02b9a38c0627258977ea7edf3e4c129ebc717e3e","tid":2197362,"uid":159271,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-09-10T14:20:00.000Z","msg":